<br>
Now, regarding weapons and the fact that your budget is ~500pp...<br>
<br>
Black Blade of Tormenting (tormenting): This would get my vote as well, just make sure your STA is over 100, cuz it's HEAVY.<br>
<br>
Short Sword of the Ykesa (ykesa): These things wil never die. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Good aggro, if not good DPS.<br>
<br>
Shaded Blade (12/24, but no procs): Okay DPS, but no proc = no added aggro.<br>
<br>
Velium Short Blade (V shards): Velium Shards are a 12 DD = no aggro. Don't bother.<br>
<br>
Glowing Black Sword (nutralize magic): I'm not sure of the aggro ability of a non-melee debuff like neutralize magic.<br>
<br>
K(something) k(something) (clinging darkness): I think you mean a Kunzar Ku'juch, which procs engulfing darkness. This would be a great weapon for your situation and price range.<br>
<br>
Gnoll Hide Lariat?? (stun??): Good aggro and fast weapon, but absolutely crappy DPS. Not recommended for your particular situation.<br>
<br>
Your problem is that you can't look for high aggro weapons, since you need to do damage and at your price range you have to choose one or the other. If you can get the druid to thorn you, ensnare and root the mob, and lay a DoT or two on it, then your aggro problems are non-existant, just go for highest damage.<br>
<br>
Having said that, I kind of like that Kunzar Ku'juch if all you have is 500pp to spend. <p><font face="sans-serif" size="2"><b>----------<br>
